572
01:11:59,100 --> 01:12:01,000
What? I beat you.
I scored.

573
01:12:04,200 --> 01:12:06,200
I'm ready to leave, 
I proved it.

574
01:12:07,600 --> 01:12:10,200
- What’s wrong? 
- You won, Ryan.

575
01:12:11,900 --> 01:12:13,800
- I didn’t. 
- No!

576
01:12:13,900 --> 01:12:16,800
You just have to believe there's more 
to life than one long winter.

577
01:12:19,500 --> 01:12:21,300
You're asking me to risk everything! 

578
01:12:22,900 --> 01:12:25,800
I've been here too long. 
I don't even remember where I came from. 


579
01:12:26,000 --> 01:12:27,800
Where would I end up?

580
01:12:29,000 --> 01:12:30,500
I can't handle that kind of uncertainty.

581
01:12:30,500 --> 01:12:32,800
Grandpa would tell you to turn all that doubt into trust.

582
01:12:32,900 --> 01:12:34,400
Take a chance, Mel!

583
01:12:35,900 --> 01:12:37,200
Do you trust me?

584
01:12:39,700 --> 01:12:41,500
Do you trust yourself?

585
01:12:43,900 --> 01:12:46,000
Do you trust yourself? 
Say it, Mel!

586
01:12:47,800 --> 01:12:49,800
Come on, get off those toe-picks
