625
01:18:52,200 --> 01:18:54,100
I never saw the Fair Footed Flekk.

626
01:18:56,400 --> 01:18:58,400
Do you know what she looks like?

627
01:18:59,000 --> 01:19:00,200
No.

628
01:19:01,300 --> 01:19:03,500
Then how do you know 
you haven't already met her?

629
01:19:12,700 --> 01:19:15,500
Funny. 
I still don’t see paradise.

630
01:19:32,300 --> 01:19:35,400
I wanna go home.

631
01:19:36,400 --> 01:19:37,400
Really go home.

632
01:19:40,900 --> 01:19:42,600
I know.

633
01:19:45,000 --> 01:19:47,000
And I don't want you to.

634
01:19:53,700 --> 01:19:55,800
It was always my plan to leave too, you know.

635
01:19:59,000 --> 01:20:01,100
But I was just waiting for a sign.

636
01:20:04,000 --> 01:20:07,200
I figured there'd be this perfect moment 
where I'd just know it was right.

637
01:20:16,300 --> 01:20:18,400
I guess I'm just a dawdler.

638
01:21:07,000 --> 01:21:10,600
You know, I can still do everything 
better than you can.

639
01:21:12,100 --> 01:21:15,400
- Faster - always will. 
- You can't always win.

640
01:21:16,200 --> 01:21:19,100
- I'll always beat YOU.
- And I won't mind.

641
01:21:21,800 --> 01:21:25,200
I’ll never forget you, Mel.

642
01:21:27,000 --> 01:21:28,100
You will.

643
01:21:28,800 --> 01:21:31,000
No, I won't.

644
01:21:33,200 --> 01:21:35,400
See you later.

645
01:21:37,600 --> 01:21:41,600
Not later. 
Just see you.

646
01:24:11,700 --> 01:24:13,900
I wish I had the courage 
to climb a mountain.

647
01:24:16,400 --> 01:24:18,400
All I have is this stupid lake!

648
01:24:23,600 --> 01:24:26,800
It’s not winter, it's not winter, 
it's not winter! It's summer! 

649
01:24:45,400 --> 01:24:46,300
Ryan!

650
01:24:46,700 --> 01:24:47,700
Ryan!

651
01:24:48,300 --> 01:24:49,200
Ryan, come on!

652
01:24:50,400 --> 01:24:51,600
